  "prompt": "How can I make friends at new job?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to make friends at a new job:\n\n1. Be friendly and approachable\n- Smile and introduce yourself\n- Show genuine interest in your coworkers\n- Be open to conversation\n\n2. Participate in social activities\n- Join team lunches or coffee breaks\n- Attend company events\n- Participate in team-building activities\n\n3. Show interest in others\n- Ask about their work\n- Listen actively\n- Share some information about yourself\n\n4. Offer help and collaborate\n- Be willing to assist colleagues\n- Work well in team projects\n- Share your skills and expertise\n\n5. Use common spaces\n- Spend time in break rooms\n- Use shared areas like kitchen or lounges\n- Strike up casual conversations\n\n6. Join workplace groups or committees\n- Volunteer for cross-department projects\n- Participate in employee resource groups\n- Join workplace clubs or social groups\n\n7. Be professional and positive\n- Maintain a positive attitude\n- Avoid office gossip\n- Be respectful and kind\n\n8. Use digital platforms\n- Connect on professional networks like LinkedIn\n- Join workplace communication channels\n- Engage in work-related online discussions\n\n9. Be patient\n- Building friendships takes time\n- Don't force connections\n- Let relationships develop naturally\n\nRemember to be authentic and genuine in your interactions.",
